<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Aggro control used to be heralded as the responsibility of the guild and not the individual tank, not so in PoP.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yes, and actually this was a problem.  Warriors were almost always preferred in most situations because you could always rely on the guild to control aggro.  That was just as much of an issue for Paladins and Shadowknights as the current situation is an issue for you.<br>
<br>
In general, it should come down to a choice.  Sometimes, a hybrid tanking should be preferred over a warrior, sometimes a warrior should be preferred.  Other times, it shouldn't ultimately matter, and it will come down to the choice of the guild.  (IE, you can use a hybrid who should be at greater risk of dying in return for more solid aggro control, or you can use a warrior who will be at less risk from dying but the rest of the guild will have to slow down a bit.  Either way the results are the same, but the actions are different) For this reason, the length of your list doesn't really help us much.  It just points out that your guild really likes to use hybrid tanks, it doesn't show that your guild is always makes the best choice or the only choice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/21/03 8:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1800.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://doug.feldmann.com/Sigurd.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No, there isn't any aggro control problem.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The fact that a 2200 hp difference did not make up for the superior aggro control of the SK is just ridiculous but it's true.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That happened because of the nature of the trials.  The ability to get and hold aggro quickly isn't always as critical as in the waves of the Exe trial. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.