<br>
I have a problem with the assertion that the cleric actually would or could run out of mana with a lesser hp tank for the end encounter.  This is PARTICULARLY true when the cleric saves a significant amount of mana over the course of the fight with the same lower HP tank.<br>
<br>
In other words.... again, if the cost of casting remedy is EXACTLY THE SAME as casting complete heal, then there's no difference between the two spells.   If over the course of the event, the cleric has to heal 2 nukers + the &quot;tank&quot; it's the same as if the tank had 1/3 the tankability as the more focused one.   Identical... that's assuming the cleric got no aggro on him or herself, in which case the efficiency is 1/4.   There is NO WAY that a cleric can sustain this type of healing without it affecting his or her mana pool at the end fight.<br>
<br>
So in other words...<br>
<br>
With SK tanking... the cleric has 4000 mana left at the end of the encounter to deal with the boss.<br>
<br>
With the warrior tanking, the cleric has (assuming that a remedy for a 2 different party members is required per CH on the warrior, which is entirely reasonable for a trial group).   The cleric would have 1500 mana to heal the warrior.   Assuming the warrior uses defensive (although the Executioner has a low DI, making it more reasonable to use evasive, spikiness is a concern with the small pool of mana available), the warrior will require approximately 4 Ch's through the fight, leaving the cleric with a whopping 300 mana... not enough to cast a 5th...<br>
<br>
The shadowknight on the other hand, even if he required DOUBLE the heals (a totally unreasonable number) would leave the cleric with 1000 mana left over.<br>
<br>
i.e. your premise is inaccurate.<br>
<br>
Finally, this notion that a tank with 2200 less hitpoints (should be a fairly dramatic difference in tankability) *should* be less mana costly is absurd.   Aggro control is one thing, but balance is entirely another.  This is NOT &quot;balanced&quot;, it's ridiculous <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frodlin7th>Frodlin7th</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/21/03 8:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1800.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No, there isn't any aggro control problem.</span><hr size=1> Goladus, <br>
