<br>
Please illustrate a common experience situation where the ability to get and hold aggro quickly is not as much of an advantage for an experience group as it is for the trials.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Pretty much any situation.<br>
<br>
In general, as a mage anyway, my average damage output in experience groups is limited by mana.  This gives me a little time to work out a nuke strategy that won't cause me to draw aggro.  My usual method is to toss one nuke on early, follow up with a click from Boots of Bladecalling(17 seconds, 600 damage if not resisted, mana-free).  By that time I should be free to toss in one or two more nukes no problem, which will probably leave me with less mana than I had at the start.  I've done this in PoD behind a pre-60 warrior wielding pre-epic weapons.<br>
<br>
The trials are different, because you are limited by time so much that mana conservation is not important.  If you don't kill a mob in the alotted time, you lose.  If you hold back to conserve mana and don't kill the immediate mob quickly enough, you lose period.  That is why I said there is a desire for &quot;unrestrained&quot; dps.  Most damage dealing classes have techiques they use to manage their aggro over the course of a session or fight, and in most cases such techniques cause a temporary dip in DPS but winds up being worth it in the long run.  During the trials, there isn't always time for these classes to properly manage their aggro, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>especially</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> if compared to experience groups.<br>
<br>
I would argue that average xp groups are probably the easiest places to manage aggro, and the place where consequences for mismanaged aggro are the least severe.<br>
<br>
Kogar's post suggests that unrestrained dps is desireable a lot more on PoP raids than it really should be, but again as I said his post simply reflects the choice of his guild, not necessarily that this is true.  Although I'll also note that at least certian situations unrestrained dps can be needed where a warrior will have plenty of time to build aggro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Tugurok:<br>
<br>
Why carry the warrior through the waves, which are the real bottleneck, when most good sks can tank the Executioner just fine, especially given the cleric is very likely to have more mana left over for the end than he would with a warrior tank?<br>
<br>
Just let the knight tank, replace the warrior with someone with more dps, and blast on through.<br>
<br>
Oh, right -- that's exactly the decision Glatius's group actually made. And it's the same decision plenty of sensible PoV/PoS experience groups are making, for exactly the same reasons. Total aggro control is worth a lot more than a minor advantage in tanking ability, when the replacement tank can do the job, which knights certainly can.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Remember I never suggested that the group will actually want to carry a warrior through the 4 waves, I said that ideally you would have a different tank for each.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ideally</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> assumes you'd have the spot to spare for an extra tank, which I admit most groups will not have.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Total aggro control is worth a lot more than a minor advantage in tanking ability, when the replacement tank can do the job, which knights certainly can.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I agree, aggro control is definitely more than a minor advantage.  However, I still don't believe warriors should automatically be as good at holding aggro as hybrids, especially if a warriors actual defensive ability IS better.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
I probably don't even have to say this but I really want to make sure I'm not misunderstood:<br>
<br>
-I don't claim to know whether or not Hybrid aggro-holding ability is too good in relation to Warrior aggro-holding ability.  I do believe hybrids should hold aggro better than warriors, though.  I believe that the ability of a tank to hold aggro is a major bottleneck for damage dealers, and giving out aggro abilities too freely would not be good for the game.<br>
<br>
-I believe that warriors should be good enough defensively to make up for their relative lack of aggro control ability in an average situation.  I don't claim to know whether or not Warriors have a suffecient advantage in this area, nor do I claim to know what the average PoP raid requires.  If Hybrids can stand up to PoP mobs whenever needed and the raid suffers no noticeable consequences otherwise then I will admit that there is a problem.  One guild's choice isn't enough to convince me, that's all.<br>
<br>
-I believe that warriors should be good damage dealers, since tanking is an ability that eventually suffers diminishing returns as you add additional tanks to a group or raid.  Warriors also generally have the least miscellaneous utility of any class, and that should count for something.  I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">definitely</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> don't claim to know whether or not warriors actually deal as much damage as they should.<br>
<br>
-I believe that the PoJ trials are naturally biased towards a high-aggro tank, and while a warrior should be good enough to get through(and they are, I've won the trials with a non-uber warrior and lost with very well equipped SKs), that any particular group finds an SK with 2200 less hp more useful isn't an indication that anything is wrong with warrior aggro control.  I would not be opposed to giving warriors more in terms of damage contribution, however. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilaara>Kilaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/03 2:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1800.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No, there isn't any aggro control problem.</span><hr size=1> Hm why do the Hybrids not see the point?<br>
